title: Four killed in latest US attack on alleged drug-smuggling boat
description: The US military have "conducted a lethal kinetic strike" on a boat that was believed to have been smuggling drugs into international waters in the Eastern Pacific Ocean, on Thursday 4th December. Four men onboard were killed during the strike in a crackdown, targeting on what the US calls, "narco-terrorists".  The US Southern Command "confirmed that the vessel was carrying illicit narcotics and transiting along a known narco-trafficking route in the Eastern Pacific". #strike #military #USpolitics #worldnews

title: Mother waits three years for answers after newborn's death | 7NEWS
description: A Western Australian mother waited three agonising years to learn why her newborn son Asha died at King Edward Memorial Hospital in 2020, due to severe backlogs at the coroner's office. The baby suffered catastrophic oxygen loss after an 11-minute delay in calling a code blue during delivery. Coronial reports taking over a year to release have increased by 30%, with the overall backlog now exceeding 1,000 cases despite calls for increased government funding.
